Final Thoughts
API security is not a one-time configuration — it requires continuous attention across the full development lifecycle. The vulnerabilities covered here share a common thread: they arise when developers prioritise speed over safety, skipping input validation, leaving old infrastructure running, or disabling logging to reduce noise.

Modules like sign-in, role-based access, and user profile settings deserve the most scrutiny — they are the most frequently targeted entry points into any system.
